name: University of Florida - La Casita
directions: Once you enter into the building, walk straight back, and it is to your right.

name: Pen Centre Mall
directions: There are washrooms tucked away behind the food court.
comment: This is a 'family' washroom, one of those where anyone can use it and there's lots of space. I have never had any trouble using it.

name: IHOP Restaurant
directions: Behind the cashier, past the kitchen.
comment: 24 hours!

name: Erikslund Shopping Center
directions: On the 1st and 2nd floor of the shopping center. Placed in the middle of each floor. Right next to the elevators.Avoid IKEA\\'s gendered bathrooms at all costs. They\\'re situated on the 1st floor. Avoid. Avoid. Trust me. It\\'s worth the extra walk. Even when you\\'re just dying to use a bathroom.
comment: Open from 10am to 8pm everyday.There are separate stalls with floor to ceiling walls - in fact more like separate bathrooms. Each stall has a easy to use lock. Good lighting and BIG mirrors.It\\'s always well kept w. soap and paper and clean floors and stalls. AND there\\'s a room for changing diapers as well. Outside on BOTH floors there\\'s lockers, big enough to put your coat and shopping bags. You need a 5 kr coin to use them. BUT you get them back when you get your things.

name: Gender/Women's Study building
directions: on the first floor, near the seminar room

name: 2720 Cherokee
directions: Main level near left side of the stage.
comment: It is a concert venue/art studio. There was a cover charge the night I was there, but I do not know if that is always the case.

name: Mount Holyoke College-Most dorms
directions: I haven't checked all the dorms, but I know that at least in Ham Hall all of the floors (except for the first floor and fourth floor) have gender-neutral bathrooms.
comment: You can only access these bathrooms if you are a student or if you are accompanied by a student.

name: King's College
directions: Two accessible, gender neutral bathrooms on the second floor of the New Academic Building. One accessible, gender neutral bathroom next to dining hall and one downstairs from the Wardroom. One accessible bathroom in the basement of the library, one of unknown accessiblility next to the Senior Common Room by the Chapel, and a couple (at least one is physically accessible) in the basement of Alex Hall, requiring signing out a key card with your ID to access. One bathroom each on the 2nd and 3rd floor of the main (A&A) building, pretty sure they're accessible.

name: Ohio Union
directions: First floor on the SW side of the building near Sloopy\\'s. It\\'s between the gendered bathrooms.

name: India Spice
comment: Bathrooms are single stall, accessible, labelled bathroom A and bathroom B.

name: University of Portsmouth
directions: 9th Floor, building does not require ID badge during daytime hours
comment: Toilet is male-gendered, however it only contains individual stalls and is used by male and female staff.

name: University of Florida - Retiz Union
directions: This is one family bathroom in the Reitz Union on the 2nd floor, right by the stairwell.

name: Chelsea Market
directions: Middle of the market/building. Near the pipe of flowing water
comment: Across from the fish market

name: Coral Ridge Mall
directions: Located in food court. Family restroom. No purchase required.

name: Dairy Queen
directions: On the left as you walk in. Gender-neutral/\"unisex.\"

name: centerra promenade shops
directions: Next to Aerospostale, across from Dicks Sporting Goods
comment: Beautiful and clean family restroom w/ locking door. 10am-9pm mon-sat, 11am-6pm sun

name: Mu Lan
comment: Restaurant is pretty bare-bones, but the tofu with dry bean sauce is amazing.

name: Holland Hall, University of Pittsburgh
directions: Top floor of Holland Hall
comment: Student ID required to enter the dorm.

name: Towers Dorms, University of Pittsburgh
directions: Every third floor of each Towers building.
comment: Student ID is required to enter the dorms.

name: Chevron, University of Pittsburgh
directions: 5th Floor of Chevron building.
comment: The building does close at night.  Generally open to all, but may be ID-restricted at certain times.

name: Market Central, University of Pittsburgh
directions: It's on the ground floor, under the cylindrical buildings.
comment: This is inside an all-you-can-eat buffet.  They charge to let you in.

name: William Pitt Union, University of Pittsburgh
directions: 6th Floor of the William Pitt Union.
comment: This floor also has the University of Pittsburgh's undergraduate LGBTQ group, the Rainbow Alliance, which holds office hours every weekday during business hours.

name: Cathedral of Learning, University of Pittsburgh
directions: 34th Floor of the Cathedral of Learning.  It's best to take an elevator to the 36th floor and walk down two flights of stairs.
comment: The building is closed to people without University of Pittsburgh IDs after a certain hour (around 11pm).

name: Kroger
directions: It's a family restroom by the pharmacy.  My husband and I went in together (we were in a hurry), and no one stopped us or even batted an eye.
comment: 24 HoursIt's a single room with a locking door.

name: USF Morsani Center for Advanced Healthcare
directions: 1st floor, in the corner by Sweetbay Pharmacy.
comment: Has a heavy-duty toilet with a wide, reinforced seat.

name: BP

comment: Store open 24 hrs.

comment: Mon-Thurs 6 am-11pm, Fri-Sat 6 am-12 am, Sun 7 am-10 pm.

name: Circle K
directions: Back of store, straight ahead from door
comment: Store open 24 hrs. Has low gas prices

name: Walden Galleria Mall
directions: There is a unisex single use restroom right next to the regular restrooms in the food court area.

name: Zhang's Chinese Buffet

name: Delta Sonic

name: El Mirador

comment: Not sure if owners would mind non-customers using it

name: Tampa International Airport
directions: At least 2:-Airside F, near entrance to Gates 76-90-1st floor, near American check-in counter & escalators

directions: In lobby next to gendered bathrooms

name: Tires Plus
comment: Customers only

name: Citgo/Presco Food Mart
directions: Back of store, down hall near coolers

name: Sligh Petrol Mart
directions: Back left of store, down hall
comment: Station also has some of the cheapest gas prices in town

name: Citgo
directions: Back left of store

name: Hamline University
directions: Walker Field House -downstairs by the racketball courts

name: Georgia Tech Clough Undergraduate Learning Commons
directions: 3rd floor.  Towards the back (away from the Starbucks) side of the building.
comment: Two one-stall bathrooms.  Clean.

name: Panda Express
directions: In the back.

name: San Francisco Art Institute
directions: On the main floor, in the quad across from the cafeteria - go in the main entrance on Chestnut Street, go through the area with the fountain keeping to the left, and walk past the campus security box and the lecture hall into the quad. Restrooms will be immediately on your right.
comment: ADA accessible, but up an incredibly steep hill! Only open weekdays - locked nights and weekends. There are fairly safe non-accessible multi-stall binary restrooms open nights and weekends: instead of bearing left and going straight past the police box, actually *turn* left at the police box and go up the stairs one flight. The bathrooms are down a long hallway on the right.

name: Red Oak Cafe
directions: It is in the back, their only restroom.
comment: Not only is the restroom accommodating but they have some awesome, local food. Carnivore, omnivore, herbivore... they have food for anyone including gluten free.

name: Harbour Bar and Fish House
directions: Go to the back of the restaurant, up the wheelchair accessible ramp and into the back door. The gender neutral bathroom's right there!

name: TexMex 2
directions: 2 single toilets, although they are gendered and quite small.
comment: Since it's a restaurant, you will have to buy something, but you could probably get away with a margarita or a Mexican beer if you don't want food.

name: Governor's Square Mall
directions: Near the exterior door by the food court
comment: this is labelled a \"family restroom\"

name: Austin Peay State University
directions: Miller Hall, ground floor. As you walk in, pass the stairs and go through the door and turn left. There is a single-stall bathroom, and around the corner there is a unisex bathroom.
comment: It's a campus building, so it's supposed to be restricted to students and staff only. However, since it's the housing office, it's not behind a locked door.

name: Superfresh
directions: Take stairs or elevator to second floor. On the east end of the building past the registers.

name: Target
directions: To the right of the pharmacy counter.

name: The Mall at Millenia
directions: In the food court.

name: UMBC Commons
directions: Commons Building, ground floor near the Yum Shoppe and Women's Center
comment: The bathroom in the UMBC Commons has recently had a few changes, and now just has a single toilet, instead of two separate stalls. There are two of these bathrooms, one on either side of the staircase. The changes were made to help ensure that people knew that it was a single use bathroom.

name: LGBT Centre for Health and Wellbeing
directions: Ring buzzer and someone will let you in.
comment: This is the LGBT Centre's location so they will definitely be a safe place. Likely to only be open certain hours, but worth a try if you need somewhere that's definitely safe.

name: Caffe Nero
comment: 2 locking single stalls, not gendered. It is very easy to get to the loos without passing by any staff. Just go in the door, up the steps, and turn right and follow the sign. Because it's a coffee shop, it's nice if you buy something but not necessary.

name: Publix
directions: To the right of the entrance, near the flower section.

name: Tijuana Flats
directions: To the left of the counter.

name: Herbert Art Gallery & Museum
directions: Main entrance by the cathedral, straight in and up the stairs (or use the lift) to the first floor, round the corner on the left, big sign - male/female/acessible. Entrance to a room with many single stalls.
comment: Museum is free, but awesome, so have a look round if you've got the time!

name: Duquesne University
directions: Zip is 15282. The one I know if is 2nd floor in Canevin Hall but there may be others on campus.
comment: It makes me so proud of my university. It's a Catholic school with gender neutral bathrooms. AWESOME!

name: Target
directions: Just to the left of the Pharmacy is the gender neutral, single person bathroom. The ones by the door are markedly gendered. Willing to bet that almost all Targets have at least one gender neutral bathroom, remember that!
comment: Target is open until 8pm during regular hours.

name: Mandel Theater
directions: Approach glass structure; ramp available. Make right, enter door that has Barnes&Nobel awning on it. Enter building, to your right is an alcove with chairs. In alcove there is a hallway on the left. Two bathrooms available.
comment: WARNING: CONSTRUCTION OCCURRING.Just act like you are a student.

name: LeConte Medical Center
directions: First floor, in the hallway between administration and the emergency room lobby.

name: Wok and Go
directions: Ground floor, to the back right.

directions: To the right when you enter.

name: UTSA

name: Chix DC
directions: 2nd floor! both bathrooms are identical anyway.
comment: I put flirt with the employees cause I'm an employee haha. But really, if you're polite and smell ok then we'll pretty much just let you go. my job is luckily very trans* and gender variant friendly.

name: Coborn's
directions: Single stall unisex bathroom in the movies section, which is by the alcohol/liquor

name: Target
directions: Top floor in the front to the left with the other restrooms.
comment: It's not completely gender neutral since there's still a male/female sign on the door, but it's not one specific gender.
